This place is honestly probably one of the worst (if not, the worst) hot pot place I've ever been to. I believe most of the previous five star ratings were because the restaurant had an event where they gifted meat platters with every five star rating.

It's $288NTD just for one soup base alone. (So another $288 for two soup bases). We ordered two soup bases, one vegetable platter, two meat platters (beef, chicken), one seafood platter (fish), one rice and three noodles for a party of four girls. Most upsetting was the quality of the soup broths and meat. The two soup broths were very bland and had an artificial taste (particularly the seafood one) which left us with an unpleasant aftertaste. For the meat, there were still pieces of bones in the beef slices and pieces of feather bits in the skin of the chicken...

It feels much of the budget was spent on exterior and interior design rather than the quality of the food. If you're looking for a place with photo ops, this could be the place for you though.
